## 4. Challenges and Solutions

| Challenge | Solution |
|---|---|
| XMLA sessions expire between conversations | Reconnect all 4 models at the start of every session — handled automatically when prompt file is pasted |
| Inventory numbers repeating across months | Root cause: HTML file corruption from a mid-script injection that split `<html lang="en">` into the JS. Fixed by reconstructing the file cleanly from the intact `<head>` section onwards |
| Weekly inventory section missing | Same corruption issue — the `buildInvTable('w-inv')` call was appended after `</html>` due to a broken string replacement. Fixed by always injecting INV data before the closing `</script>` tag |
| `website_quantity` misinterpretation | Documented as OFFLINE reserved stock in both knowledge files with explicit warning — never show by default |
| NPS queries returning wrong dates | Explicit `USERELATIONSHIP` added to every NPS query — no auto-link between NPS and the main date table |
| Availability measure names differ between models | `FAST - Test _new` (Cont A) vs `FAST - Test` (Core) — both documented in memory file with a do-not-swap warning |
| Country filter understating online revenue | `country = "IN"` filter removed from all-India queries — documented with explanation |

